<BLOCKQUOTE>Posted by
Radek on 13:21:49 9/22/1999 from 24.6.53.96:<p>
In reply to: <a href="http://cor.simplenet.com/Mage/mageboard.mv?parm_func=showmsg+parm_msgnum=1000188">Give me one reason not to quit !! (long)</a> posted by 
Celarye on 12:34:46 9/20/1999 from 195.249.161.203:<p>
34 it gets better.<br>27-33 are hell levels for Magicians.. 30 especially since we did not get a damage spell, and are still using shock of spikes and its' pathetic 176 damage. 34 you get Blaze (294 at my level) and Cinder Bolt (333 at my level)<br><br>34-38 magicians have the highest DD of any class. We outpower Wizards, even. Our 34 pets are not disapointments by far - I used my earth elemental exclusively, and while it is not a root, it is a DOT. We do become group oriented, though. We don't get root, true. Root is very useful, but thats why you group with someone who does have root... which sadly is basically everyone else in the game. <grin><br><br>I spent 34-36 in Lower Guk Dead side by the zone, killing the froggies there, solo or going into the bedroom with a group. I now stay in Lower Guk, way down by the Reanimated Hand and the Ghoul Magi, or with the Sonic Bats and Nox Spiders in Nagafen. I am wanted. I walk into Lower Guk.. Radek shouts, 'Level 42 Magician looking for group, perferrably not insane' and I get a reply pretty fast. - I still do very nice DD for 44, I can summon Levitate rings (a lot of the reason people want me.. summon 2 rings for each tank. <grin>) and my pet.<br><br>I've never had a train problem with my pet since I removed Malise from my hotkey list and replaced it with a macro for /pet guard here. If your pet is sitting, it doesn't make trains. If something gets away, it's gonna train you no matter if you have a pet on it or not. It doesn't make any difference. It's better to have the pet on it, IMHO because it stays away longer, giving everyone more time to recupporate. Of course, then everything comes back at the Magician, so make sure you inform your cleric or shaman to be on the ball to heal you.<br><br>If something is leaving, you can also /pet back off very fast and it won't cause a "bigger train" (Common myth.. doesn't happen but some people have a problem with your pet leaving with a mob)<br><br>Level 44 is going to be a treat.. shock of swords is another glimmer of hope -- Cinder Bolt doesn't work in Nagafen. Blaze doesn't work very well. I still use shock of spikes there, so thats why you see me in Lower Guk more often.<br><br><br>Anyway -- done ranting. Time to go kill things.<br><br>Radek Miragel<br>Magician, level 42<br>Bertoxxulous
</MvEVAL>
</BLOCKQUOTE><hr width=90%><p>
